The paper describes the development of a deep learning model for the automated detection of celiac disease on duodenal biopsy slides. This involves the analysis of images, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.DL) sub-categories. The paper also involves the analysis of medical data, which suggests that it may belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the technology on medical diagnosis, which suggests that it may belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
